article.headline: TCU 81, Colorado St. 67
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Keion Mitchem scored 19 points and Zvonko Buljan added 18 for TCU, which beat Colorado State 81-67 on Saturday night in the conference opener for both teams. Kevin Langford added 16 points and Edvinas Ruzgas had 10 for the Horned Frogs (9-5, 1-0 Mountain West). Willis Gardner, who was 8 of 10 from the field, had 23 points to lead Colorado State (5-10, 0-1). Marcus Walker scored 16 points. The Horned Frogs shot 54 percent from the field, including 65 percent in the second half. TCU took a 34-31 halftime lead before outscoring the Rams 47-36 in the second half.
